Vice President Mike Pence delivered a speech at Miller Electric Company in Jacksonville, Florida, highlighting the Trump administration's efforts to promote job training and vocational education. Pence praised the company for its apprenticeship program and its commitment to creating job opportunities. He also discussed the administration's achievements in deregulation, energy production, and tax cuts, which have contributed to a booming economy and record-low unemployment rates. Pence emphasized the importance of expanding vocational education to meet the demand for skilled workers in various industries. He also mentioned the success of the Pledge to America's Workers initiative, which has created 12 million job training opportunities. Pence concluded by encouraging the audience to continue supporting policies that promote economic growth and job creation.